{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdHDdKJitBYUDPH9rNUiQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Root cause found.** The regex is:\n\n```\n/^[^\\s@]+@[A-Za-z0-9-]+(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]*)*\\.[A-Za-z]{2,}$/\n```\n\nThe domain-label group `(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]*)*` uses `*` (zero-or-more) for the label characters, so a `.` followed by *nothing* is a valid match. That lets consecutive dots (`..`, an empty label) through — exactly contradicting the file's own comment (\"Labels must be NON-EMPTY\"). The existing test suite never exercised a multi-label or empty-label domain, so it passed for months.\n\nLet me confirm the reproduction, add a failing test, then fix at the source."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2099,"cache_read_input_tokens":24549,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2099},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8341789d-7d94-432d-bf6c-fce68013f0fd","uuid":"7cf63e45-9885-4559-85c6-98f604a2ae68","timestamp":"2026-07-22T14:01:47.993Z","request_id":"req_011CdHDdFaF4K2NT1wTCNt7R"}
